Indiana Pacers to Promote Frank Vogel to Head Basketball Coach, ESPN Says

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-07-06T04:36:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/indiana-pacers-to-promote-frank-vogel-to-head-basketball-coach-espn-says.html
The  Indiana Pacers  will introduce
Frank Vogel as their new head basketball coach today,  ESPN
reported .  Vogel and President of Basketball Operations Larry Bird
will hold a news conference at 11 a.m. at Conseco Fieldhouse in
Indianapolis, according to the team’s website.  Vogel, 38, replaced Jim O’Brien in January as interim coach
and directed the Pacers to their first playoff berth since 2006.
The Pacers went 20-18 under Vogel and lost to the  Chicago Bulls 
in five games in the first round of the postseason after
finishing eighth in the Eastern Conference.  Vogel started his National Basketball Association career as
a video coordinator for the Boston Celtics. He worked for the
Philadelphia 76ers, Los Angeles Lakers and  Washington Wizards 
before joining the Pacers as an assistant to O’Brien.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
